Fed a hungry squirrel in Golden Gate Park, had lunch at John’s Grill that was featured n the Maltese Falcon. Got some cools pictures in Union square. Good day.
Also. I should clean my mirror.
Walking on, walking on broken glass!
Since I’ve still got a BOX FULL of broken glass in the shop from Flyfleaf, I’m not keeping this. But I’m more than up for another broken glass project if you have any ideas!!
New video live on YouTube. Link in bio. Come see what I do with over 6lbs of resin on my lathe!!

I bought this set in 2015 to send them to SmarterEveryDay but he messaged me on Reddit and said he didn’t want them. So they’ve sat in a drawer for 7 years. Just pulled them out yesterday on Christmas. Super fun to play with. :)

I tried to increase the amount time spent walking this year. 

I feel pretty good about the progress thus far.
Fake snow and some other crazy ideas.

New Dye Trying up on YouTube! Come celebrate in our Post Holiday Dye Experiment Extravaganza!

2023 vibe thus far.

Yes. Those are tree tops. :)
They call it a bomb cyclone or an atmospheric river. It is a LOT of water.

Thanks to @letsresin for some new products to try out. Love the Jellyfish! Excited to give this a go.
 
Who’s got ideas you would love to see happen in 2023!?
The sculpture of Michael Cooper on exhibit at the Sonoma County Museum!  Amazing use of wood and curves like I’ve never seen before!
Found myself at Rays Salvage in Sebastopol this weekend. Place is an amazing spot. Yes, they even have the kitchen sink. Multiple, I believe.
We got a little sunshine. But I’m gonna need to rig up some sort of a holder for this thing. It’s sort of cumbersome.
New Video out on YouTube! Link in the bio.
My first laser. I feel like we should name this little guy.
Grown up fall.

You’re not supposed to take wooden nickels but how about copper quarters? Pulled out the @enchantedleaves setup for some electro forming ideas.

Out of the splint. Into the cast. 
Dr: “Nobody picks lemon yellow”
If I have to look at it for 6 weeks it should be cheerful!
Work in progress. Copper forming some kind objects in the shop! @enchantedleaves

New video out! Link in bio. 

Busted wing means no large power tools, so I’m spending some time learning the laser and messing with copper plating!

Sold my CNC machine today. It’s been sitting there since 2017. Feels super odd to have that space open. 

Fret not my friends, I’m sure we’ll fill it up!!
I’m going to try and copper plate and patina some copper with new extremes for me. Both in size and in the amount of oxidation! We’re going full Statue of Liberty for this project. Link in bio.
Dart cast hack! I’ve found a use for this thing.
Haven’t quite solved my shifting problem yet.

Off for X-ray. Can you see how my left arm atrophied for a while in hibernation. 

With any luck I’ll graduate to a splint. No luck means another cast!
What are we making?
A bunch of super cars just showed up in Victoria outside the hotel.
Heron nest at Beacon Hill Park.
Getting setup for glamour shots. Project video incoming soon.
You asked for a Whole Sprinkle project. I’m trying to deliver. YouTube link in bio!

My light box, can also be a shadow box. Such versatile. So amaze.

New video up. You asked if we could engrave on a single corn kernel with the @xtool.official P2. 

I aimed to find out. Link in bio.

Power Tools In The Dark. 
I’ve checked in with Mr. Safety Cone. Video up on YouTube. Link in bio.
A new project has begun.
Pretty sure this a legit tattoo kit. What should we do with it!? I’m not volunteering…

My new YouTube video isn't supposed to be a weight loss post. It was supposed to be feeling comfortable with yourself.

I'm not in great shape, but I "feel" better, and since you all have been asking in my videos for a while, I wanted to share my progress. 

I made a small change 4 years ago, and I don't feel "bad" anymore.

Excited to see you at @opensaucelive. 

Just say hello, I would love to meet you!

My youngest daughter requested we snap this picture for her, so we did that first thing!! 

That sorted, we can now check that off the booty bucket list and move on to what must be lesser experiences. @opensaucelive
It was so nice getting to talk with @evanandkatelyn at @opensaucelive. We had a great event. Hope you two have a safe flight home!!

I caught @joeltelling stealing a 200lbs+ metal Transformers 3d print at the close of @opensaucelive 
He showed no remorse for his crime.
I found @williamsunpetrus and his wild-looking machine at the @opensaucelive event! William came all the way to San Francisco from Scotland to show it off!
Getting close to wrapping up on this project. Might be my most ambitious in a few years! So many colors!!!

Is this Stained Glass? New video up on YouTube! I hope you like it, link in my bio!

I think this turned out really well. Let me know what you want to see next!!
My friend @jlwritebol took us to an AMAZING 4 story used book store in Detroit Michigan. So cool!

I decided to make a handle out of brownies! I then decided that I had made a HORRIBLE MISTAKE. I then decided to make a handle out of BRICK.
Why do I do these things to myself?!

New video up on YouTube, link in the bio

Dye Trying: Back 2 School! Edition is live on YouTube. We test out ideas for dyes and pigments within the back to school theme! 

Hope you enjoy the successes and failures!!
#Link in bio.
Working on another stained glass project. The mess is always impressive.

More Resin Stained Glass but using your suggestions from the last video!!

This project is in your hands…

Look at this amazing work of art that was sent to me by Colleen. 

I’m pretty sure this was all drawn with pens!!?
Haha! What’s the matter Colonel Sanders? Chicken?

Waiting at SFO for our flight to Rome. Never been to Italy before. Really stupid excited. 

I’m always nervous before a flight not because I’m worried about crashing but because I’m a control freak. Think I’m on track to get two miles of walking in at the terminal. 

If the Captain needs anything I’ll be sharp and ready in my seat.

Arrived in Rome last night. Took at walk around to get good and tired before bed. Here is the Pantheon at 5pm and then at 5:30am. 
There are a lot of us tourists here. I like both vibes. One is crazy chaos and one is more peaceful but both feel good. 

#beneroma

If you want to walk to the top of St. Peter’s in Rome it cost 8 Euro and is a 551 step ascent. Completely amazing view. 2/3 of the way up you can get a pretty stunning view inside the church before the last bit to the very top. 

I’ve earned some pasta I think.
At Maker Faire Rome! Walking round practicing poor Itialian. @makerfairerome
So much to see @makerfairerome !!
Oh MAN!! @odd_jayy found Jay at Rome! How cool is that. He’s in the @digikey booth. Say Ciao @makerfairerome

Got to meet my friend Yuval @yuval_lahav_woodturning  in Rome. He showed us around and it was great to catch up!! We talked about Caesar, cats and wood turning! Look he’s even wearing @easywoodtools apparel! 

Thank you brother for a great afternoon!!

Got to meet up with my friend Thomas. @monkwerks Father Thomas has been living in Rome for the past 5 years, but will be headed back to states soon. It was great to catch up. Go check him out his channel is called MonkWerks.
Headed back home today. Had a fantastic time in Rome. Thank you for the historic,chaotic and lovely indulgence.

New video live on YouTube. Link in bio. 
Egg-citing project!
Our last day in Rome we spent 45 minutes in @ikono.roma no one asked our opinion but I think you should check it out if you have the opportunity. A fun feast for the senses.
A cool experiment I found @makerfairerome in October. I’m a huge fan of black lights. You know I had to go into these tents.
I think it would be super effective.
Green Lantern is up on the tree. Maybe he’ll get some respect this year. :)

One of my favorite Christmas decorations is this reindeer from @krtwood 

If Kevin is making them again, get one. You won’t regret it. :)
Double dyed eggshell stopper video is live on YouTube. Link in bio. Also, turned a gold handled kitchen utensil fit for the Palace at Versailles.
Vintage glass molds for resin. New video is live on YouTube! Link in bio. Hope you enjoy it!! 🥽👷
Merry Christmas Internet. My teenagers aren’t awake yet so, Mrs. Brown and I are getting a second cup of needed coffee. :)

My friend Chris stopped by and he wanted to try out the F1. In under a minute it performed a clear etch on both sides of his blade. 
We then celebrated that blazing success with a delicious meal. 😜😂
Is this how Prof. Slughorn felt when Tom Riddle reached out to him?
Just a geek with a full set of power tools!
